UniCredit’s Russian Unit Starts Syndicating $300 Million Loan

-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 
2011-07-06T15:07:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/unicredit-s-russian-unit-starts-syndicating-300-million-loan.html
ZAO UniCredit Bank, the Russian unit
of  Italy ’s biggest bank, started syndicating a $300 million term
loan to fund trade finance and its business.  Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd., Commerzbank AG,
UniCredit Bank Austria AG,  Wells Fargo & Co . and WestLB AG are
arranging the three-year facility that pays interest of 150
basis points more than the London interbank offered rate, the
banks said in a statement today.  Standard & Poor’s rates ZAO UniCredit’s debt BBB-. Fitch
Ratings ranks it BBB+. A basis point is 0.01 percentage point.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
